HEADWORD: Hydracrylic
<hw>Hy`dra*cryl"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hydr-</ets> + <ets>acrylic</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Pertaining to, or designating, an isomeric variety of lactic acid
that breaks down into acrylic acid and water.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

